Here are some things You can do with Linux Terminal

Basics:

1. Opening something specific in a browser : xdg-open https://www._____________.com
2. Opening anything: application name (e.g.. google-chrome)

Watching Anime:
installation: sudo apt install ani-cli
use command: ani-cli 

# Those were some basic stuffs now let's talk about some fun stuffs:

1. Opening a Retro TV style Terminal : 
          installation: sudo apt install cool-retro-term
          use command: cool-retro-term

2. Virtual Cat chasing Cursor:
          installation: sudo apt-get install oneko
          use command: oneko

3. Display Digital Clock:
          installation: sudo apt install tty-clock
          use command: tty-clock

4. Display in stylish text:
          installation: sudo apt-get install figlet
          use command:
                      normal: figlet ________.
                      change font: figlet -f slant ____.

5.Aquarium simulation in Ascii:
                    installation: sudo snap install asciiquarium
                    use command: asciiquarium

6.Train simulation in Ascii:
                    installation: sudo apt install sl
                    use command: sl

7.Virtual Fire:
          installation: sudo apt install libaa-bin
          use command: aafire

8. Text-to-speech:
          installation: sudo apt install cowsay
          use command: cowsay ____.

9. Random Fortune teller:
          installation: sudo apt install fortune-mod
          use command: fortune

10. Network test:
            installation: sudo apt install speedtest-cli
            use command:
                      basic command: speedtest
                      in bytes: speedtest --bytes
                      server list: speedtest --list

11. Tetris Game:
          installation: sudo apt install bastet
          run : bastet

12. Cmatrix:
          installation: sudo apt install cmatrix
          run: cmatrix 

13. General search in terminal:
                    installation: sudo apt install ddgr
                    run: ddgr ___.
